{{one source|date=October 2015}} The '''graphic telescope''' is a type of [[camera lucida]] that has the power of a [[telescope]]. It was invented by [[Cornelius Varley]]<ref>[http://www.mhs.ox.ac.uk/cameras/index.htm?item17 picture of a Graphic telescope]</ref> in 1811.
