'''Symphony No. 1 "Low"''', also known as the '''''"Low" Symphony''''', is a [[symphony]] by [[Philip Glass]] based on [[David Bowie]]'s album ''[[Low (David Bowie album)|Low]]''.

In 1996, Glass based [[Symphony No. 4 (Glass)|another symphony]] on David Bowie's following album ''[["Heroes" (David Bowie album)|"Heroes"]]''.

==The symphony==
The symphony was composed in 1992 and scored for full orchestra with 2 [[flute]]s, [[piccolo]], 2 [[oboe]]s, 2 [[clarinet]]s, [[E-flat clarinet|E{{music|flat}} clarinet]], [[bass clarinet]], 2 [[bassoon]]s, 4 [[French horn|horns]], 3 trumpets, 3 [[trombone]]s, [[tuba]], percussion, [[harp]], piano and strings (including 8 first [[violin]]s, 6 second violins, 4 [[viola]]s, 4 [[cello]]s and 2 [[double bass]]es).

The symphony has three movements:

{{Ordered list|type=upper-roman
|[[Subterraneans]]
|[[Some Are]]
|[[Warszawa (song)|Warszawa]]
}}

"Some Are", the David Bowie song on which the second movement was based, didn't feature on the original release of Low but was recorded during the Low recording sessions. The song would later be released on the [[Rykodisc]] reissue of David Bowie's album in 1991.

==Recordings==

The first recording of this work was released in 1993 under the title ''Low Symphony''. It was performed by the [[Brooklyn Philharmonic]] orchestra under the batons of [[Dennis Russell Davies]], principal conductor, and Karen Kamensek, assistant conductor.<ref>[http://www.philipglass.com/music/recordings/low_symphony.php Philip Glass: Music: "Low" Symphony<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110520085211/http://www.philipglass.com/music/recordings/low_symphony.php |date=20 May 2011 }}</ref> [[Philip Glass]] allowed ideas of Bowie and [[Brian Eno]], who worked together on [[Low (David Bowie album)|Low]], to influence how he worked on the music.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.philipglass.com/music/recordings/low_symphony.php |title=Philip Glass: Music: "Low" Symphony |publisher=philipglass.com |accessdate=18 February 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110520085211/http://www.philipglass.com/music/recordings/low_symphony.php |archivedate=20 May 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

# Subterraneans (16:08)
# Some Are (11:11)
# Warszawa (19:24)

